      "message": "The raw .so files have a line like:\nGROUP ( /usr/arm-linux-gnueabihf/lib/libpthread.so.0 /usr/arm-linux-gnueabihf/lib/libpthread_nonshared.a )\nThis doesn\u0027t work because the bots won\u0027t have those as an absolute path.  I replace those lines with\nGROUP ( libpthread.so.0 libpthread_nonshared.a )\n\nfileinput.input redirects stdout to be an inline replacement of the file contents, so printing here actually allows for a \none line replacement, while keeping the rest of the contents there.\n\nComment added to clarify.",
